%MA4003 Week 13 Cholesky /Jacobi

Find the Cholesky decomposition ($A = LLT$
) of the matrix 5
\[
A =
\left(

4 & −2 & 0 \\
−2 &2 & 1 \\
0 & 1 & 20\\

\right)
\]
and hence solve the system of equations Ax = b where 3
b =

−2 \\
0 \\
−8 \\
\right)
\]

\newpage

\begin{itemize}
\item a^2=1 \therefore a=1	
\item ab=3 b=3
\item ad=1 d=1	
\item b^2+c^2=13 \therefore c^2=4 \thefore c=^2
\item bd+ce=7	\therefore e=^2
\item d^2+e^2+f^2=6		\therefore		f=1
\end{itemize}

	       
%=======================================================================%


MA4003                                          
 Linear Algebra                            
Cholesky Decomposition

%=========================================%

\begin{itemize}
\item a,b,c,d,e,f are real number coefficients
\end{itemize}

\[ 
L^T = 
\begin{array}{c c c}
a &  0 & 0 \\ 
b & c & 0 \\ 
d &  e & f \\ 
\end{array}  
\]

 

\[ 
L^T = 
 
\begin{array}{c c c}
a &  b & d \\ 
0 & c & e \\ 
0 &  0 & f \\ 
\end{array}  

\]

%=============================================================% 

A = L \times L^T  


 \[ 
L^T = 
\begin{array}{c c c}
a &  0 & 0 \\ 
b & c & 0 \\ 
d &  e & f \\ 
\end{array}  
 
\begin{array}{c c c}
a &  b & d \\ 
0 & c & e \\ 
0 &  0 & f \\ 
\end{array}  

= 

\begin{array}{c c c}
a^2 &  ab & ad \\ 
0 & b^2+c^2 & e \\ 
0 &  0 & d^2 +e^2 + f^2 \\ 
\end{array}  
\]

%=============================================================% 

 

A Input matrix:


 1.000 -2.000  1.000

-2.000 20.000 -2.000

 1.000 -2.000 10.000


Cholesky Decomposition:


L:

 1.000  0.000  0.000

-2.000  4.000  0.000

 1.000  0.000  3.000


Solution A*X=B


